                h2 Research 

                p Because saving the pollinators is a big concern across several agencies, I began to look at what others were doing to raise awareness about pollinators. One of our partners, the Xerces Society for Invertebrate Conservation, specialises in pollinator conservation. They had a myriad of materials to look through and compare. 

                p The <a href="https://500px.com/leejeffries">Lee Jeffries</a> portfolio provided inspiration for the final product. 

                p To help model the butterfly looked through the <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/usgsbiml/">amazing collection</a> USGS has on FlickreUSGS portfolio of Bee inventory. I also searched in Google images for profile and facing camera images of butterflies. 


            section
                h2 The Journey

                p When our team met about this newsletter we knew the theme was pollinators, but wasn’t sure what we wanted to convey the message as. Our inspiration images included before/after images of what a supermarket produce section would look like without pollinators, we had come across a comic strip that portrayed a homeless be willing to work for nectra, we explored pollinators being super hero group like the Avengers. We settled on the super hero team and moved forward. 

                p In my spare time, I had been working on developing my photography skills and was looking at how to take better black and white photos. In doing so I came across the portfolio of Lee Jeffries who takes portraits of the homeless. His images are able to to tell a story, you are able to see the pain, suffering, personality, and hope in his images and it stuck with me. 

                p On my walk from my car to the office I began to think back to the comic strip and was thinking we could apply the style of <a href="https://500px.com/leejeffries">Lee Jeffries</a> to the <a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/lowres.cartoonstock.com/animals-nectar-bee-insect-bug-hive-tmcn3996_low.jpg">comic strip</a> to create a compelling story that pollinators need habitat and food. 

                p I presented my idea to the team and it was received with great enthusiasm. We shifted gears and I began thinking of how I could best accomplish this. I had experience with an open source 3d software called Blender 3D and figured I could model the butterfly in that program, used the program to provide the appropriate lighting and then do the final touches in Photoshop.

