                p Once I had my images, I set to modeling. The key to creating emotion in the image was modeling the antennae to look a bit dejected, leave the legs in an almost hanging position, the rest was really the lighting. It is high contrast and while there isn’t much rim lighting in Lee Jeffries images, I decided it helped bring focus to the butterflies face, to offset the amount of white that was in its body.  

